						<summary>

						<p>On the north base of the Karivaradarāja-perumāḷ temple.</p>						

						<p>This damaged inscription, of which the beginning is lost, in characters of about the <hi rend="bold">12th century,</hi> seems to record the order of the king, granting of land and incomes from levies as <hi rend="italic">abhishēka-dakshiṇā</hi> to god Karumāṇikkāḻvār and of paddy for offerings and for the reciters of <hi rend="italic">Tiruvāymoḻi.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
